OL,3,C'Devastating cuts' to support for
OL,4,Cadopted children leaving parents
OL,5,Cpetrified
OL,7,FThe Department for Education announced
OL,8,Fin April that the annual therapy
OL,9,Ffunding limit was being reduced by
OL,10,F40%, from #5,000 per adopted child to
OL,11,F#3,000.
OL,13,FMinisters claim the changes are needed
OL,14,Fto ensure that the maximum possible
OL,15,Fnumber of children are able to receive
OL,16,Ffunding for therapy.
OL,18,FBut Rachel, from Worthing, says the
OL,19,Fchanges will be 'devastating' for her
OL,20,Fprimary-school-aged son, who has been
OL,21,Freceiving weekly therapy for two years.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
